name: Columbia Mall
directions: On the bottom floor by the food court. There's an elevator down nearby in Sears. There are two regular multi stall gendered bathrooms but there are also 2 family/unisex stalls.

name: Monroe Community College
directions: Building 5, first floor.
comment: This bathroom is open to all, one stall, and the user is encoraged to lock the door. Nice decor and kept clean.

name: Stanley Residence Hall, Iowa City, IA 52245, USA
directions: All bathrooms on all floors
comment: Need a student ID or prox card to enter building

name: Stella's Kentucky Deli
comment: Open Restrooms Single Person. Welcoming environment.

name: Target
directions: to the left of the entrance is a "family" restroom.

name: Mohegan St, Syracuse, NY 13209, USA
directions: Next to the 4-H Youth Building, by the small stage. Accessible by wheelchair.
comment: Single stall restroom labeled unisex. Near binary, multi-stall restrooms. Seems unobtrusive.

name: Aragon High School
directions: Two bathrooms on opposite sides of center court.

name: Picadilly Artisan Creamery
directions: In the back, to the left

name: Ramsey County Library / Dunn Bros Coffee
directions: Two unisex single stall restrooms down a small hallway in the coffee shop attached to the library. Out of sight of the counter, though you do have to pass it to get there.
comment: Since the coffee shop is attached to the library it seems to me like they don't care if you purchase anything.

name: Wesley United Methodist Church
directions: One on the main level between the front door and the large staircase, another (less visible) on the lower level in a corner close to the elevator.
comment: The church doors are not always unlocked but they are on Sunday morning and early afternoon.

name: North Park Branch Library
directions: 2 individual restrooms to the right as you enter.

name: University Heights Branch Library
directions: 2 single restrooms at the back of the library.

name: Olivet Nazarene U - Reed Hall
directions: Lower level hallway

name: Kensington branch library
directions: Just inside front door.

name: 2601 S Lemay Ave, Fort Collins, CO 80525, USA
directions: Walk in to Starbucks and to the right. Two gender neutral bathrooms.

name: United Airlines Club
comment: Must be a United Airline member to enter the club and use restrooms

name: William H. Gates Hall, University of Washington School of Law
directions: The nearest to the main (east) entrance is on the right, past the staircase, to the left of the elevator.
comment: Building is open to the public Monday through Friday, 8 AM - 5 PM. There is a multi-stall, all-gender restroom near the main (east) entrance on the first floor to the left of the main elevator. All multi-stall gendered restrooms in the building are marked with a sign indicating that all individuals are welcome to use the facilities of the gender with which they identify.

name: Caffe Vit√°
comment: For paying customers.

name: Bay Books
directions: Ask for the key at the front counter. Head to the back of the store; its on the right, right after the classics.
comment: The staff are very nice :)

name: Pies & Pints
directions: In the back, in a bit of a side hallway.
comment: Single stalls, just marked "restroom." I think they are reasonably accessible (flat ground, standard size doorways), but unfortunately I am not aware of all of the criteria in this area!

name: Williams Insulation
directions: Ask the person working to use the bathroom don't just walk in
comment: It's a single stalled gender neutral bathroom

name: Kohl's
directions: Way back of the store one the left
comment: There are two multi stall gendered bathrooms but there's also a family bathroom that isn't gendered

name: Seattle Healing Arts
directions: Second floor

name: flirt cafe bar
directions: Straight through the main exit, just past the bar.
comment: If it's quiet you should probably buy something.

name: Huntington Hall
directions: Off the Jacquet Commons by the door to Suite 150

name: Wildfire Gymnastics
directions: Just past the registration desk
comment: They have two, single occupancy, gender neutral restrooms

name: The Tea House at Los Rios
directions: Downstairs, next to the women's restroom.
comment: Browse in the store for a moment, if you'd like.

name: Open Barbers
directions: At the back on the right
comment: This is a gender neutral barber shop and safe social space that is inclusive of all genders and sexualities. It is specifically queer and trans friendly.

name: Genesis Cinema
directions: The single stall accessible restroom is located just across from the Kiosk
comment: Just ask at the box office to go in to use the toilet, you don't have to buy anything

name: HEP Thrift Store
directions: On right wall of fitting rooms, beside shoes section
comment: Two gendered single stalls, labeled 'men' and 'women'. Moderate visibility. Accessible to all whether or not you're purchasing something.

name: University of Manchester Student Union
directions: On the right hand side of the main entrance.
comment: You're completely welcome no matter who you are.

name: Bryn Mawr College
directions: Almost all the restroom on Bryn Mawr's campus are gender neutral. A few of the older buildings might have both gendered and non-gendered, but the vast majority are gender neutral. It is also a very supportive space LGBTQ+ students to be in general :)

name: Palo Verde Clubhouse
directions: Across from the mailboxes.
comment: Free access, however parking is restricted to residents. Might get a ticket if parked for too long.

name: BirnKrant Residence Hall Lobby
directions: Just behind and to the right of the security desk
comment: You must be either a USC student or the guest of a USC student to access this building

name: Birnkrant Residence Hall Lobby
directions: Just behind and to the right of the security desk
comment: You must be a USC student or the guest of a USC student to access this location

name: Thriftwood Scout Campsite
directions: Walk up the main track from the main gate.
comment: If the gate is locked just ring the buzzer and ask if you can use the toilet.

name: Kronshage Residence Hall
directions: Walk in the main entrance (that faces the lake). The bathroom is on the left in the main lobby (near the main office).
comment: You must be a hall resident, a guest of a resident, or employee of the university to access this residence hall (and bathroom).

name: The Wedge Table
directions: left of the coffee counter, just past the community room and classroom on the left

name: Liquid State
directions: 2 single stalls in the back. No gender designation; just  pictures of toilets.
comment: They are a small, friendly business. You should probably be a customer, but I think they would understand if you weren't.

name: Liquid State
directions: 2 single stalls in the back. No gender designation; just  pictures of toilets.
comment: They are a small, friendly business. You should probably be a customer, but I think they would understand if you weren't.

name: Salem College Fine Arts Center
directions: Go through the front door all the way to the back, then turn right. At almost the end of this hallway on the righr there is a small side hallway with two unisex single-stall restrooms. If you see another exit, you went too far.

name: Salem College Student Center
directions: On campus, go to the center of campus and find the building with the glass doors. Go in, around the staircase, past the help desk,and to the left. There is a women's room and a unisex bathroom.
comment: Doors close to non-students at 9pm.

name: Super Target
directions: There is a family/private restroom where the two gendered restrooms are, as well as one by the pharmacy.
comment: Not sure they would notice one way or another whether you were a paying guest or not, but then again, it's Target, and there's always something to spend all the monies on :)

name: Zumi's Espresso
directions: By the back entrance.
comment: Accessible entrance in the back.

name: Legislative Assembly of Alberta
directions: Main floor, east and west wings
comment: Accessible to the public, though typically only if you are visiting on tour or on business. Other floors' bathrooms are not gender neutral.

name: Benildus Hall
directions: Far right of the building when entering from the front. There's two.
comment: Multiple stalls. Both were converted from gendered restrooms so one still has urinals. Very safe. Students are aware.

name: Fogelson Library Center
directions: On campus, first floor.
comment: Librarian is an ally. If you have any problems, ask for Sierra.

name: Hewlett Packard Enterprise
directions: Just past the security desk,  on the left.
comment: You need a badge or to be buzzed in by security to access the building.

name: Vassar Alumnae House
directions: Enter Alumnae House from the front entrance and walk through the lobby toward the elevator. Before you get to the elevator you will see two doors, one with a sign that says Garden Level. Head through that door and down the stairs, continuing straight down the hallway at the end of the stairs. Enter the Production Room on your left. The bathroom will be on the left side of the room.
comment: This is technically an employees-only bathroom but students that not everyone in the offices knows work here as well, so if you look college aged and act like you're supposed to be there you should be able to get in and out with no questions asked. Probably not the easiest place to get into if you don't look college aged, however, since most of the adults here know each other.

name: Starbucks
comment: If you walk in the door that's facing the highway, the restrooms are in the opposite direction as the counter, so it would be easy to slip in and out without having to buy a drink.

name: Postino Central
directions: When you walk in the door, the restrooms are in the very back right corner, next to the kitchens.
comment: There are two single-stall restrooms labeled "Both".

name: Boyer Center for molecular medicine
directions: First floor lonby
comment: You have to have a Yale ID to enter the building

name: The Public Theater
directions: In the back left of the lobby
comment: Available to anyone!  Private stalls, gender-neutral.

name: The crossing
directions: Once entering the crossings front doors, it is up the stairs/elevator and directly to your left.
comment: A residence hall and retail complex

name: Muhlenberg College Seegers Union
directions: Main floor. Go straight when you walk in. There is a male, female, and gender neutral bathroom.
comment: It's a college.

name: North Carolina museum of art
directions: Two in the education wing of the East building, one by the elevator at the back of the building on level A

name: Canadian Light Source Inc.
directions: Up the big ramp to the front door. The receptionist can buzz you in. Ask for a washroom and you will be directed to across the lobby area.

name: Dicecup cafe
directions: Through the shop up the ramp and to the right.
comment: It's best if you buy a drink or something. The guys running the place are all friendly and the toilets also have a baby changing mat, sanitary bins in both.

name: Starbucks
directions: Downstairs at the back
comment: You have to be a paying customer, there are two toilet cubicles.

name: Subway
directions: Upstairs
comment: You are supposed to be a paying customer

name: American University Hughes Hall
directions: one on either side of the lobby
comment: ask the desk receptionist to point you toward the restroom, you should be able to use it without an ID that is needed to get upstairs since it's a residence hall

name: Dollar General
directions: In the back of the store
comment: Ask a cashier for a key

name: Dollar General
directions: In the back of the building, in a little "hallway"
comment: You have to ask a cashier for a key

name: Bridge City Middle School
directions: It's in the nurse's office!!!

name: Pita Pit
directions: Behind the booths.
comment: Gender-neutral single stalls with wheelchair access. Bathrooms are clean, and the food at Pita Pit is good.

name: San Diego International Airport
comment: Accessible to all people after passing security check for flights!

name: JJ Thai Street Food
directions: In the back.
comment: It's a restaurant, so you do have to be a paying customer.

name: 7 eleven
directions: To the right of the slushee machine

name: Earth Sciences Building, UBC
directions: One unisex single stall per floor, located between the gendered washrooms near to the atrium
comment: The adjoining building EOSC Main has a unisex, accessible bathroom only on the first floor. The remaining floors have gendered bathrooms but they are single stall and seem to be rarely used.

name: Hive Climbing Gym
directions: 3 bathrooms - 1 unisex in the training room, 2 gendered but with signs indicating they are safe for trans people and anyone caught staring or commenting will be ejected
comment: It's pretty out of the way so you probably wouldn't be there unless you were actually climbing. They won't care if you aren't though.

name: Safeco Field
directions: Between section 333 and 335

name: Crabbe Library, 457 University Dr, Richmond, KY 40475, USA
directions: To the left of Java City Cafe in the library. Signage is posted with directions to the cafe from 2/4 entrances. Library staff can help someone find it from one of the other entrances.
comment: Bathroom is only handicap accessible from the main entrance. Contains a working lock, but does not have a child changing station. You do not have to buy anything from the cafe. Bathroom is accessible during the library's hours of operation.

name: Edge Brewery
directions: 2 gender neutral single stalls,  near the front

name: Le Pita
directions: Forward and left frontage entrance.
comment: Probably need to order something, but they have cheap things to-go. May be accessible, wide door and handrail by toilet.

name: Prefunk
directions: To the left of the bar,  gender neutral single stall

name: Goodnow Library
directions: When you walk into the front doors of the library take a left into the children's section and it's right on the right. It's meant for handicapped and or parents with there children so because of that its unisex.
comment: Don't have to be a paying customer, It's a library

name: Ted's Most Best
directions: 2 restrooms straight back on the left.

name: Charlotte International Airport Gate C7
directions: By gate C7 family restroom.
comment: Past security

name: Durham College
directions: Student Services Building; Rooms SSB 216A and 216B

name: Kent State Student Center
directions: Third floor of the Student Center, 330B left of the elevator.
comment: Universal bathroom sign, ADA single stall.

name: H√∏gskolen i Lillehammer
directions: There are unisex bathrooms by auditorium C and D, plus E, on third floor. There's also unisex bathrooms by SOPP bok, which is through the handicap lavatory door, which is on second floor. There's also a unisex bathroom in a separate building (brown), which is a handicap bathroom.
comment: The University College is pretty open, just look like a passing student and you will be fine.

name: Araya's Place
comment: Two single stall restrooms located near the middle of the restaurant.

name: Walmart
directions: Its a family bathroom. Its in the very back of the store, to the right of Site to Store/Lay away(during the holidays). It is right in the middle, between the men's and women's restrooms.

name: Cupcake Royale
directions: To the left of the counter in the far back
comment: Grab a key from the back of the counter (to the left of the espresso machine).

name: El Gallo Giro
directions: Off the seating area left of the front door
comment: Customers only,  I think.

name: Cava Grill
street: Tysons Corner Center, 1961 Chain Bridge Rd
directions: To the left and back of the restaurant (not the hallway next to it)

name: King Soopers City Market
directions: To the right of the pharmacy there is a family restroom

name: Colusa Hall
directions: Entering the building from the wheelchair-accessible entrance on the west side, walk straight until you see the signs (one on each side)
comment: Two single-stall, all-gender restrooms (on CSU campus but no ID card needed, only open during school hours)

name: Bell Memorial Union
directions: Downstairs (elevator located next to coffee shop) and to the left (opposite from the coffee shop)
comment: Three single-stall bathrooms marked as accessible for all genders
